  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Prevention Strategies:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious activities\n- Financial institution compliance checks\n- Criminal penalties for violations\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement investigations\n- Asset seizure\n- International cooperation\n- Substantial financial penalties\n\n5. Specific Regulatory Requirements:\n- Record-keeping obligations\n- Transaction reporting\n- Risk assessment procedures\n- Background checks\n- Enhanced scrutiny for high-risk transactions\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions and financial sectors.",
